Patch Set 1:

@RichBennett Better doc is always good - as of now I don't know how to correctly build master branch. I would like to build the doc and also apply my local changes (files, git repo) to see how the result looks and to polish it. The only way how to build it is to skip broken submodules - if your procedure is different and more robust then maybe it would be great to post it somewhere so people can replicate it and have their own copy of the docs locally and in exactly the same shape.

Another question: So when and how the master will be fixed? Currently it is impossible to build the docs with tox -elocal without my fix...are we waiting for people from ccsdk/cds repo to fix this?
